<TITLE> Nine Rajshahi policemen suspended for negligence in duty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com) -- Nine policemen, including two officers, were suspended temporarily on Wednesday night on charge of negligence in duty during Tuesday's clashes at Rajshahi University that left a student killed and scores of others injured. The order came hours after home minister Sahara Khatun warned of action against negligent law enforcers. The suspended policemen include Rajshahi Metropolitan Police sub-inspector Anwar Hossain, assistant sub-inspector Mohsin Alam, nayek Al Mamun, and constables Naimul Haque, Arifur Rahman, Ishak Ali, Monwarul Islam, Abbas Ali and Khairul Islam. RMP deputy commissioner Sarder Nurul Amin told bdnews24.com that those suspended policemen were on duty at Shah Mukhdum Hall during the incident. Faruk Hossain was killed in a clash between cadres of Bangladesh Chhatara League and Islami Chhatra Shibir at Rajshahi University in the early hours of Tuesday. Chhatra League leaders alleged that half-hearted action of the law enforcers was responsible for the death of Faruk. bd
